transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra. How can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Yes, ma'am. My name is Ronald Pack, P-A-C-K.

Speaker 1: Mm-hmm. I just ordered some—

Speaker 2: Bag, what's the new bag called, bigger A-T-C or something like that. Okay.

Speaker 1: And you sent me this—

Speaker 2: So I can fill.

Speaker 1: Okay, um, do you have the pills with you, Ron?

Speaker 2: I have them on hand right now.

Speaker 1: Okay, um, can you take a look at the pills? Do they have a number 50 engraved on them? One second, I have to take it apart.

Speaker 2: Yes, they can, yes.

Speaker 1: I'm coming.

Speaker 2: You're still there?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Hello?

Speaker 1: Yes, 339 in Grayville.

Speaker 2: Okay, so it sounds like you got the classic Viagra wrong and not the AGV.

Speaker 1: So I'll notify the pharmacy so that they reship the correct Viagra AGV for you, okay?

Speaker 2: And then I'll go ahead and I'll pause your VIP till March so that you have enough time to try it.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: What do you want me to do with the ones in my hand?

Speaker 1: Don't worry about having to return them back to us.

Speaker 2: You can go ahead and keep them or discard them, up to you, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay, have a good rest of your day, Yvonne. Bye.
